Baby Release 3.0 is mine...and needcoffee.com is an excellent idea!  (I'll also be registering needdiapers.com, needsanity.com, and needsleep.com...)



So how _would_ you check that?  Server logs?  NTFS will only track file copies if auditing is turned on.  I'm not familiar with how Novell handles things, nor *nix.  (although I'm sure they both have logging facilities...just not sure what's "common" configuration wise)  Hmm...although av software can be configured to scan files as they cross the NIC (although for a busy file server that could be a potentially nasty load) and just might have a log.



"Clean the laptop"...does that mean a reformat, DOD 5220.22-M wipe, or "she deleted the files and emptied the recycle bin"?  The last would be fairly straightforward to recover from, but the others...?



"curiouser and curiouser" said Alice...</span>
